         <div part="N" org="uniform" sample="complete">
            <head>THE NEGRO SPEAKS OF RIVERS</head>
            <lg part="N" org="uniform" sample="complete">
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">I’ve known rivers . . .</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">I’ve known rivers ancient as the world and older than the flow</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">of human blood in human veins.</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">My soul has grown deep like the rivers.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg part="N" org="uniform" sample="complete">
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">I bathed in the <placeName instant="false" full="yes">Euphrates</placeName> when dawns were young,</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">I built my hut near the <placeName instant="false" full="yes">Congo</placeName> and it lulled me to sleep,</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">I looked upon the <placeName instant="false" full="yes">Nile</placeName> and raised the pyramids above it.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg part="N" org="uniform" sample="complete">
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">I heard the singing of the <placeName instant="false" full="yes">Mississippi</placeName> when</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">
                  <name full="yes" instant="false">Abe Lincoln</name> went down to <placeName instant="false" full="yes">New Orleans</placeName>,</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">And I’ve seen its muddy bosom turn all golden in the sunset.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg part="N" org="uniform" sample="complete">
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">I’ve known rivers:</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">Ancient, dusky rivers,</l>
               <l enjamb="no" part="N">My soul has grown deep like the rivers.</l>
            </lg>
            <byline>-Langston Hughes</byline>
         </div>
      </body>
